cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with neural language models and their application in Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR). Additionally, it may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as ASR involves processing audio signals. It could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural language models are a type of machine learning algorithm and fall under the umbrella of AI. Finally, it may also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses solutions to challenges in implementing NLM in a practical large-scale ASR system.
